                    <p>Why is this so complicated ? Free markets system  : Winner takes all, Loser loses all. The first part is happening very nicely. But the second part is not. It is essentially the fear of losing all which drives people to make the right decisions. Ideally all banks that went bust, should have gone bust and not bailed out. Yes, home prices will fall, markets will crash, joblessness will be high for a few painful years. But this will create a foundation or platform for a better generation in future and most leaders would be careful not to repeat the folly.</p>
